@node "history" "The History of ETrashCan"
@{b}Version 1.0 (29.11.95)@{ub}
    First (locally) distributed version


@{b}Version 1.1 (10.12.95)@{ub}
    Added support for seperate icon images for full and empty
    trashcans.
    First Aminet release

@{b}Version 1.2 (16.12.95)@{ub}
    Now a commodity, using Fabios' cxobj_oo module.
    Removed the 'About/Quit' button from the requester.
    Can be controlled via exchange
    (quit, hide and show appicon)
    Rather unstable

@{b}Version 1.3 (21.12.95)@{ub}
    Rewrote commodity code myself. Now stable, and saved
    500 bytes :-)

@{b}Version 1.4 (4.1.96)@{ub}
    Fixed bug causing frequent crashes using default icons.
    Fixed two enforcer hits (I just got enforcer running, which
    is why I didn't spot them before)
    Default icon changed to the program icon, rather than WBGARBAGE.

@{b}Version 1.5 (7.1.96)@{ub}
    Added undelete facility and GUI
    Second Aminet Release
@endnode

@node "hidden" "hidden"
'Deleted' files are moved into a directory called ':trashcan' on the same
volume. If it does not exist when needed it will be created. Files can be
recovered from here manually, or with ETrashCan's @{"gui" link "gui" 0}.
@endnode

